%% Training Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
%% Source: architecture/rhoai-2.25/training-operator.md

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Client
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    participant Operator as Training Operator<br/>opendatahub namespace
    participant Worker1 as Training Worker Pod 1<br/>user namespace
    participant Worker2 as Training Worker Pod 2<br/>user namespace
    participant HeadlessSvc as Headless Service<br/>DNS discovery
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>openshift-monitoring

    Note over User,Prometheus: Flow 1: Training Job Submission

    User->>K8sAPI: POST PyTorchJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token/Certificate
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>TLS (self-signed), API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation Response (Allowed/Denied)
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR Created / Rejected

    Note over Operator,HeadlessSvc: Flow 2: Reconciliation & Resource Creation

    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event: PyTorchJob created
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Pods (master + workers)<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Headless Service<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create PodGroup (optional)<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token

    Note over Worker1,Worker2: Flow 3: Distributed Training Execution

    Worker1->>HeadlessSvc: DNS lookup for peers
    HeadlessSvc-->>Worker1: Pod IPs
    Worker1->>Worker2: Training data exchange<br/>TCP (plaintext, user-defined)<br/>NetworkPolicy enforced
    Worker2->>Worker1: Gradient synchronization<br/>TCP (plaintext, user-defined)

    Note over Operator,Prometheus: Flow 4: Metrics Collection

    Prometheus->>Operator: GET /metrics<br/>HTTP/8080, plaintext, no auth
    Operator-->>Prometheus: Prometheus metrics

    Note over Operator,K8sAPI: Flow 5: Job Completion

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update PyTorchJob status<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Cleanup resources (optional)<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
